# ==============================================================================
# DATA ENGINEERING BOOTCAMP - MASTER GITIGNORE
# ==============================================================================

# ------------------------------------------------------------------------------
# 1. SECURITY & CREDENTIALS (CRITICAL)
# ------------------------------------------------------------------------------
# In this bootcamp, you will handle GCP/AWS Service Accounts. 
# We ignore all .json files by default because leaking a key to GitHub 
# can lead to unauthorized cloud usage and high costs.
*.json
keys/
secrets/
auth/
.env
.envrc
*.pem
*.ppk

# NOTE: If you must commit a non-sensitive JSON config file, 
# use: git add -f filename.json

# ------------------------------------------------------------------------------
# 2. DATASETS & LARGE FILES
# ------------------------------------------------------------------------------
# GitHub is for code, not data. Files >100MB will fail to upload.
# Your scripts should download the data; the data should not live in the repo.
*.csv
*.parquet
*.jsonl
*.avro
*.gz
*.zip
*.tar.gz
data/
dataset/
temp/

# ------------------------------------------------------------------------------
# 3. TERRAFORM
# ------------------------------------------------------------------------------
# .terraform: Contains heavy provider binaries.
# .tfstate: Contains the "blueprint" of your infra. It often includes 
# sensitive metadata and should NEVER be shared.
.terraform/
*.tfstate
*.tfstate.backup
*.tfvars
*.tfvars.json
.terraform.lock.hcl

# ------------------------------------------------------------------------------
# 4. DOCKER & DATABASE PERSISTENCE
# ------------------------------------------------------------------------------
# When you mount a volume for Postgres (e.g., pgdata/), thousands of 
# system files are created. These are for local use only.
pgdata/
*_data/
.docker/

# ------------------------------------------------------------------------------
# 5. PYTHON & ENVIRONMENTS
# ------------------------------------------------------------------------------
# Removes compiled code and local virtual environments to keep the repo clean.
__pycache__/
*.py[cod]
*$py.class
.venv
venv/
env/
ENV/
.pytest_cache/
.ipynb_checkpoints
.mypy_cache/

# ------------------------------------------------------------------------------
# 6. IDE & SYSTEM FILES
# ------------------------------------------------------------------------------
.vscode/
.idea/
.DS_Store
Thumbs.db